Enlarged meeting of CILRECO executive committee held 

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 11 (KCNA) -- An enlarged meeting of the executive committee of the International Liaison Committee for Reunification and Peace in Korea (CILRECO) was held in Brussels on February 6.
   The meeting focussed on the issue of waging an active international solidarity movement in support of the Korean people's just cause to open an epochal phase of national reunification in view of the dangerous situation prevailing in the Korean peninsula and the policy of dependence on outside forces and confrontation with the DPRK which the present "government" of South Korea is pursuing.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Guy Dupre, secretary general of the CILRECO, in his report noted that the solidarity movement for the reunification of Korea should focus  on putting pressure on the U.S. to respond to the conclusion of a peace agreement with the U.S. troop pullout as its core.
   The world peace-loving people who advocate the reunification and peace of Korea should fully support a letter to the South Korean authorities and political parties, organizations and personages of various social strata at home and abroad adopted at a joint meeting of the DPRK government, political parties and organizations and wage an active international solidarity movement for its realization, he stressed.
   A letter to General Secretary Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting. 
   An appeal to governments and socio-political forces of different countries around the world and international organizations and an action programme of CILRECO for 1999 were also adopted.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The appeal called upon governments and socio-political forces of different countries around the world and international organizations to put pressure on the U.S. to respond to a proposal for the replacement of the Korean Armistice Agreement with a peace agreement, to stop interference in the internal affairs of Korea and to withdraw its troops from South Korea. It also called upon them to fully support the proposal adopted at the joint meeting of the DPRK government, political parties and organizations and to urge the South Korean authorities to accept this proposal.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A special resolution of the enlarged meeting of the executive committee of CILRECO was adopted at the meeting.
   Considering the DPRK's new offer to the South Korean authorities and political parties, organizations and personages of various social standings at home and abroad to be a very important one at the present juncture because it is designed to thwart the danger of a new war in the Korean peninsula and to reunify the country in reliance upon great national unity, it fully supports the proposal, it noted.

Proposal of joint meeting of DPRK government, political parties and organisations 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 11 (KCNA) -- Vice-chairman Ko Tae Chol of the central committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea (NDFSK) on February 9 released a statement in support of a proposal of a joint meeting of the DPRK government, political parties and organizations, Seoul-based radio Voice of National Salvation said.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He voiced full support for the recent proposal of the north for opening a new phase of national reunification through national independence and great unity, saying that it is an epochal measure of national salvation and reunification to bridge over the prevailing situation and open a new phase of national reunification.
   He further said:   The present authorities of South Korea should discontinue such anti-national, anti-reunification actions as seeking "cooperation" with outside forces against the fellow countrymen, staging  frantic joint military maneuvers, keeping the "National Security Law" in force and suppressing patriotic champions of reunification. They should at the same time make a policy switchover  at an early date and go in for national independence and pro-north reconciliation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The NDFSK, as well as broad segments of people, will accelerate a march for independence and reunification and thus greatly help make this year a year of national independence and great unity in hearty response to the three charters of national reunification set forth by the President Kim Il Sung and the five-point policy of great national unity laid down by General Secretary Kim Jong Il.
